# Dockerfile.jre is a base-only image (no ENTRYPOINT) — USER is set by downstream Dockerfile.
# Dockerfile, Dockerfile.local and Dockerfile.native all set USER explicitly, so this
# global suppression in practice only hides the Dockerfile.jre finding.
AVD-DS-0002

# terraform/storage.tf: ai_images_public bucket is intentionally public.
# AI-generated images are served directly over HTTP from GCS to the FE for speed
# (no backend proxy in the hot path). Only applies to the ai_images bucket.
AVD-GCP-0001

# terraform/cloud_sql.tf: Cloud SQL keeps public IP (ipv4_enabled = true) on purpose
# so that local development can connect via Cloud SQL Auth Proxy (`make db-proxy`).
# Cloud Run still reaches the DB over private IP through the VPC connector — public IP
# only exists for the proxy connection, which is authenticated via IAM and encrypted.
AVD-GCP-0017
